The paper deals with detecting attacks on deep learning systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of model interpretability and object detection techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the susceptibility of neural networks to attacks, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the need for defenses against such attacks, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
